Reasoning: The paper deals with optimization and hierarchical structure discovery in sequential data, which are common topics in computer science. The use of algorithms and computational complexity analysis suggests that it could belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The application of the framework to text compression and feature extraction suggests that it could also belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. The use of optimization techniques and the focus on minimizing the number of concatenations suggests that it could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The use of DNA synthesis and protein sequences suggests that it could belong to the cs.CC (Computational Biology and Bioinformatics) sub-category. Finally, the use of dictionaries suggests that it could belong to the cs.DB (Databases) sub-category.
